<div class="index-hero container">
    <div class="hero-description-column">
        <h1>The Distributed Design Learning Hub</h1>
        <p class="hero-description">Designing circular, resilient, collaborative, and just futures is complex.</p>
        <p class="hero-description">
            This Learning Hub aims to provide resources and practical learning materials to support you in exploring new topics, navigating intersectional practices, and expanding your knowledge. The Hub is collaboratively developed with the <a class="monochrome"
    href="https://distributeddesign.eu/"
    target="_blank">Distributed Design</a> community and further expanded through the European-funded project <a class="monochrome" href="https://www.makeathek.eu/" target="_blank">make-a-thek</a>.
        </p>
        <p class="hero-description">
            Currently you can find more than
            <span class="stat"><span class="n">{{ stats.total_documents }}</span>&nbsp;resources</span>
            curated in
            <span class="stat"><span class="n">{{ stats.total_themes }}</span>&nbsp;thematic areas</span>
            containing
            <span class="stat text"><a href="{{ url_for("format", format="text") }}"><span class="n">{{ stats.total_text_format }}</span>&nbsp;publications, papers & reports</a></span>,
            <span class="stat audiovisual"><a href="{{ url_for("format", format="audiovisual") }}"><span class="n">{{ stats.total_audiovisual_format }}</span>&nbsp;masterclasses, documentaries & podcasts</a></span>,
            <span class="stat tool"><a href="{{ url_for("format", format="tool") }}"><span class="n">{{ stats.total_tool_format }}</span>&nbsp;toolkits, methods & frameworks</a></span>, and
            <span class="stat course"><a href="{{ url_for("format", format="course") }}"><span class="n">{{ stats.total_course_format }}</span>&nbsp;interactive learning resources</a></span>
            from more than
            <span class="stat"><span class="n">{{ stats.total_unique_authors }}</span>&nbsp;different authors</span>.
        </p>
        <p class="hero-description">
            Choose a <span class="theme-hint">thematic area</span> from the list to get started, or search for your own <span class="search-hint">area of interest</span>.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-themes-column">
        {% for theme in themes %}
            <div class="theme">
                <a class="btn" href="{{ url_for("theme", theme_name=theme) }}">{{ theme }}</a>
            </div>
        {% endfor %}
        <div class="query-form-container">
            <form action="{{ url_for("query") }}" class="query-form" method="get">
                <input type="text"
                       name="query"
                       placeholder="Or any other theme or topic..."
                       required />
                <div class="submit-button">
                    <span class="emoji">
                        <input type="submit"
                               name="Submit"
                               aria-label="Create a personalised theme page"
                               value="âž•" />
                    </span>
                </div>
            </form>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
